<br>
We've already been through the over-aggro situation years ago.  A classic example I remember was two groups fighting near each other at HG's in RM.  As a bard, sometimes not only would I steal aggro off the tank, but the freaking HG the group next to me was fighting would disengage from that group and come beat on me as well.  Was nice getting accused of KS'ing like that.  Very broken.<br>
<br>
As pointed out many times over, we don't want anyone or anything messing with current song aggro.  Therefore, the main solutions to create aggro are:<br>
1)  A special song/ability to do so.  Obviously this should come at a cost either taking up a slot in twist or AA points.<br>
2)  Items.  This currently exists but I'm not sure how hate procs really work for bards vs. non-bards.  Some say equal to any other class.  Others I've heard say not the same.  Another option is bard only weapon procs.  /shrug.<br>
3)  Other.  Here we get into new and exotic ideas.  Probably the least workable of the 3.  Things like a taunt button with 3x other classes refresh time on it and lower success rate.  New non-aa skills, etc.  I just don't see, at this point, any of this happening.<br>
<br>
Sorry, but bored so feel free to pick it apart.  Well, 'cept for #3 since I think that is weak already.<br>
<br>
<br>
Edit:  You know, I'm about sure it's not doable, but some sorta skill/AA/whatever that allowed us to go from the old bard aggro rules(most likely aggro like a caster) to new bard aggro rules would be a hoot.  I'd like to try it for a week just for old-times where bard dies first.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
